<dl id="n12167g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12167g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12167g"> 167(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> took human life</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">WORK FOR IRELAND&apos;S BENEFIT. / WHAT THE GOVERNMENT HAS ACHIEVED. / ARCHBISHOP&apos;S TRIBUTE. / <font color="green">[Most Rev. Dr. Curley, Archbishop of Baltimore&apos;s words:]</font> &hellip; &ldquo;De Valera&apos;s irregulars blew up bridges by the hundreds, robbed banks, wrecked and looted trains, <mark>took human life</mark>, destroyed and plundered private homes without a shred of noble purpose in their destructive work.&rdquo; <small> <a name="II19sep24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#II19sep24"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (19 September 1924) 5/1</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12168h" href="c12all.htm#c12168h">VI.C.12:168(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
